{"id": "611", "instruction": "What is the integral $\\oint_{| z |=1} \\frac{2 \\mathrm{i}} {z^{2}+2 a z+1} \\mathrm{d} z \\,, a \\! > \\! 1$?\n\nOptions:\nA. $$-\\frac{2 \\pi} {a^{2}-1}$$\nB. $$-\\frac{2 \\pi i} {\\sqrt{a^{2}-1}}$$\nC. $$-\\frac{2 \\pi} {\\sqrt{2a^{2}-1}}$$\nD. $$-\\frac{2 \\pi} {\\sqrt{a^{2}-1}}$$\nE. $$\\frac{2 \\pi} {\\sqrt{a^{2}-1}}$$\nF. $$\\frac{\\pi} {\\sqrt{a^{2}-1}}$$\nG. $$-\\frac{2 \\pi} {\\sqrt{a^{2}+1}}$$\nH. $$-\\frac{2 \\pi} {\\sqrt{a^{2}-2}}$$\nI. $$-\\frac{\\pi} {2\\sqrt{a^{2}-1}}$$\nJ. $$-\\frac{4 \\pi} {\\sqrt{a^{2}-1}}$$", "output": "D"}
